cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper is about optimizing deep neural networks using Hessian-free training, which is a popular technique in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these categories are closely related to the topic of deep neural networks. Additionally, the paper mentions using these techniques for speech recognition tasks, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper also discusses optimization algorithms, which could potentially fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
